What is ASTM standard for concrete coring?
ASTM C42 Core Requirements

Minimum core diameter is 3.70 inches or at least two times the nominal maximum size of the coarse aggregate, whichever is larger. Smaller diameter cores are allowed for slabs as long as the core length is equal to or greater than the core diameter.

Tilt-up, tilt-slab or tilt-wall?? is a type of building and a construction technique using concrete.
Tilt-up construction is a proven system in which concrete wall panels are cast on-site and ‘tilted’ into position using cranes. This results in a faster construction process than other methods, such as precast and concrete blocks, and is more cost-effective as well

The firefighters remove a nozzle or two, fasten hoses to the nozzles and turn the valve to get the water flowing.

Rebar Inspection‼️ Inspection of the reinforcing steel in concrete forms is done by visual examination of the layout scheme and by measurement of bar spacing and physical counting of bars. Bar grades, diameters, shapes and bends can also be checked visually; embedments and bearings on walls and beams are checked visually as well.

water content in a batch of concrete.
“Slump” is the
distance, measured in inches, the concrete settles
after the slump cone is removed. .
.. Keep in mind that
the more water in the mix, the higher the risk of cracks.
